## Information

See folder2ram manual (man folder2ram).

## How to

To use it, you need to :

Define the mountpoints that will be handled by folder2ram in '/etc/folder2ram/folder2ram.conf'.
You can find an example in the auto-generated configuration file

## Inspiration

folder2ram was born because I was not satisfied by fs2ram. 
It borrows the core idea of bind-mounting from
the script written by mcortese in 2010
in this webpage https://www.debian-administration.org/article/661/A_transient_/var/log
webpage saved as mht and available in docs folder
